-- Serena Williams Wins Fourth Wimbledon Title, Defeating Zvonareva 6-3, 6-2
-- Rob Gloster
-- 2010-07-03T13:50:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-03/serena-williams-wins-first-set-6-3-against-zvonareva-in-wimbledon-final.html

          
          
             Serena Williams won the first set of
the Wimbledon women’s final, serving six aces and breaking Vera
Zvonareva’s serve in the eighth game to win 6-3.  
 Williams, 28, an American, is the defending champion and
the top seed. She is seeking her fourth Wimbledon title. No. 21
Zvonareva, 25, a Russian, is in her first Wimbledon final.  
          
          


  


        